"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839030","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-02-22","<p>We have no record of any discussions between Ministers in this Department and the Equality and Human Rights Commission regarding the Planning Policy for Traveller Sites published in 2015.</p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab",,"2018-02-22T17:05:26.237Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839030/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839030/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839030/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-02-08","Travellers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, what discussions Minsters of his Department have had with the Equality and Human Rights Commission on the effect of the revised definition of Traveller in PPTS 2015 in relation to local planning authorities’ policy provision.","false","Biography information for Kate Green","Stretford and Urmston","Kate Green","127590"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839031","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-02-20","<p>Before Pay As You Earn (PAYE) data is used by Universal Credit, an individual’s details are validated against both the DWP Customer Information System and HMRC’s Citizen’s Identification Framework to ensure they match between both government departments. This ensures the correct HMRC PAYE data is being used by Universal Credit for each individual. If the details do not match, the cases are investigated manually.</p><p> </p><p>Once an individual’s details have been successfully matched the HMRC Real Time Information System sends PAYE data to the DWP Real Time Earnings System. As the PAYE data is received, the DWP Real Time Earnings System performs a series of validation checks to ensure the correct PAYE data is used in Universal Credit payment calculations. This process validates for missing or incorrect data, including duplicate data, and also validates for Employer corrections and errors.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2018-02-20T11:40:46.207Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839031/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839031/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839031/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-02-08","Universal Credit: PAYE","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what steps her Department takes to validate the PAYE data it receives from HMRC on the amounts paid to claimants of universal credit.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","127591"
