"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839101","Department for Transport","false","2018-02-22","<p>Network Rail continually assess level crossings to either close or reduce their risk by carrying out upgrades and improvement work. This ongoing process is done to ensure the safety of both crossing users and the travelling public. The funding for specific safety projects is a matter for Network Rail.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson","127661","2018-02-22T16:19:31.61Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839101/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839101/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839101/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-02-08","Level Crossings","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what the timetable is for the next round of funding for railway safely projects to be allocated to the closure of level crossings.","false","Biography information for Chris Elmore","Ogmore","Chris Elmore","127660"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839102","Department for Transport","false","2018-02-22","<p>Network Rail continually assess level crossings to either close or reduce their risk by carrying out upgrades and improvement work. This ongoing process is done to ensure the safety of both crossing users and the travelling public. The funding for specific safety projects is a matter for Network Rail.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson","127660","2018-02-22T16:19:31.673Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839102/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839102/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839102/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-02-08","Level Crossings: Closures","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what the timetable is for the next phase of level crossing closures.","false","Biography information for Chris Elmore","Ogmore","Chris Elmore","127661"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839103","Department for Transport","false","2018-02-26","<p>Network Rail has committed to releasing land for homes to support the government’s housing goal of building 1.5 million homes between 2015 and 2022.</p><p> </p><p>Network Rail itself has not built any housing units for rent or sale, and nor has its contractors. Network Rail releases surplus land to sell to developers. The current programme of sales is expected to enable developers to build around 12,000 homes for the period of 1 April 2015 to 31 March 2020. Having sold the land, Network Rail does not have control over nor tracks the number or type of houses built.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2018-02-26T13:24:50.573Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839103/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839103/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839103/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-02-08","Network Rail: Housing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what information his Department holds on the number of housing units for rent or sale built by Network Rail or its contractors since 2013.","false","Biography information for Ian Mearns","Gateshead","Ian Mearns","127662"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839104","Wales Office","false","2018-02-20","<p>The UK Government is investing record amounts in modernising this country’s rail infrastructure, including a £5.7bn investment in high-tech IEP trains. Responsibility for maintaining the safety of our railway operations lies with Network Rail and the Train Operating Companies, and they will assess the safety impact of any change on the network to ensure that this is delivered safely.</p><p> </p>","Vale of Glamorgan","Alun Cairns",,"2018-02-20T09:39:31.637Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839104/answer","Biography information for Alun Cairns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839104/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839104/answer",,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2018-02-08","Railways: Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, whether he has made representations to the Secretary of State for Transport on the railway safety implications of the cancellation of rail electrification programmes in and to Wales; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Chris Elmore","Ogmore","Chris Elmore","127663"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839105","Department for Transport","false","2018-02-26","<p>Network Rail generates over £200m each year from stations and property assets, money which is reinvested back into the railway to create a better railway for Britain.</p><p> </p><p>Network Rail’s investment into railway-owned land and property assets improves experiences for passengers and also creates opportunities to work with third parties to provide new residential and commercial space, driving growth and regeneration in our towns and cities.</p><p> </p><p>Network Rail itself has not built any units for rent or sale for commercial use. Its contractors have built units for commercial use, but Network Rail does not hold information on the number of units built by its contractors across its estate.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2018-02-26T13:27:34.673Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839105/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839105/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839105/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-02-08","Network Rail: Housing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what information his Department holds on the number of units for rent or sale for commercial use built by Network Rail or its contractors since 2013.","false","Biography information for Ian Mearns","Gateshead","Ian Mearns","127664"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839106","Department for Transport","false","2018-02-26","<p>Network Rail itself does not build housing units for rent or sale, and nor does its contractors.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2018-02-26T13:30:27.447Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839106/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839106/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839106/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-02-08","Network Rail: Housing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many housing units for rent or sale his Department estimates Network Rail or its contractors will have built by 2020.","false","Biography information for Ian Mearns","Gateshead","Ian Mearns","127665"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839107","Department for Transport","false","2018-02-26","<p>Network Rail does not hold estimates of the number of commercial and retail units to be built by 2020.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2018-02-26T13:35:15.917Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839107/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839107/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839107/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-02-08","Network Rail: Housing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what estimate his Department has made of the number of units for rent or sale for commercial use which will be built by Network Rail or its contractors by 2020.","false","Biography information for Ian Mearns","Gateshead","Ian Mearns","127666"
