"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839161","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-02-20","<p>DWP has not undertaken any research on this specific topic.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2018-02-20T12:38:04.637Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839161/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839161/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839161/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-02-08","Social Security: Personal Income","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, if he will publish the research his Department has (a) conducted and (b) commissioned into Basic Income schemes since 2010.","false","Biography information for Dan Carden","Liverpool, Walton","Dan Carden","127719"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839162","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-02-20","<p>Entitlement to benefit is not dependent on a specific diagnosis, meaning that claimants may apply at any age above the minimum age requirement specific to each individual benefit claimed.</p><p> </p><p>For those diagnosed with dementia, once the impact is such that a person has care or mobility needs which may give rise to additional costs, they may apply for a disability benefit.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2018-02-20T15:02:18.453Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839162/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839162/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839162/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-02-08","Social Security Benefits: Dementia","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, at what age a person with dementia is eligible for benefit entitlement as a result of that condition.","false","Biography information for Gordon Henderson","Sittingbourne and Sheppey","Gordon Henderson","127720"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839163","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-02-20","<p>DWP is committed to refreshing the information deposited in the House of Commons Library on Universal Credit on a regular basis, including when there are significant changes, such as those announced at the Autumn Budget.</p><p> </p><p>The Budget changes are being introduced through the early part of 2018 and will all be implemented by the end of April 2018. I will update the Library in full at that time.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2018-02-20T12:28:13.577Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839163/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839163/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839163/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-02-08","Universal Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, if he will place in the Library a copy of the revised guidance issued to staff as a result of the changes to universal credit announced in Autumn Budget 2017.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","127721"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839164","Home Office","false","2018-02-20","<p>UK Visas and Immigration use various methods when returning valuable documents to its customers, this is clearly set out to customers as part of the application process. Customers have the option to arrange recorded or special delivery should they wish. Or to apply using our premium routes which allows them to make an application without giving their documents up at all.</p><p>When we are informed of errors we work promptly to rectify them, including the loss of valuable documents. Customer feedback, including complaints, are taken into account to ensure we offer value for money; which includes improving the services we offer, the quality of the decisions we make and the provision of an excellent customer service.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2018-02-20T12:10:18.96Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839164/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839164/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839164/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-02-08","UK Visas and Immigration","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, if she will make an assessment of the effectiveness of UK Visas and Immigration's practice of returning important personal documents including (a) passports and (b) birth certificates by standard post.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","127722"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839165","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-02-23","<p>The Department is engaging with the very limited number of parties interested in delivering Collective Defined Contribution pensions. The Government is considering what, if any legislation would be appropriate and await detailed proposals once the parties have made their position clear. There is currently no timetable for presenting legislation to Parliament. The Department has recently responded to the Work and Pensions Select Committee.</p>","Hexham","Guy Opperman",,"2018-02-23T12:01:29.717Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839165/answer","Biography information for Guy Opperman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839165/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839165/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-02-08","Occupational Money Purchase Schemes","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what the timetable is to present to Parliament, the secondary legislation required to enable Collective Defined Contribution pensions.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","127723"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839166","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-02-26","<p>Officials at the Department have commented on drafts of the Sustainable Access to Innovative Therapies report as it has been developed.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2018-02-26T17:34:43.347Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839166/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839166/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839166/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-02-08","Medical Treatments: Innovation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what evidence his Department submitted to the OECD's report on Sustainable Access to Innovative Therapies.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","127724"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839167","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-02-20","<p>The Ministry of Defence currently holds contracts with the following Government strategic suppliers.</p><p>Accenture</p><p>Atos</p><p>Babcock International Group PLC</p><p>BAE Systems PLC</p><p>British Telecommunications PLC</p><p>Capita PLC</p><p>Carillion PLC</p><p>DHL</p><p>Engie</p><p>Fujitsu Ltd</p><p>Groupe CGI</p><p>DXC/HP</p><p>International Business Machines Corporation</p><p>Interserve PLC</p><p>ISS</p><p>Microsoft Corporation</p><p>Oracle Corporation</p><p>Serco Group PLC</p><p>Sodexo</p><p>Sopra Steria</p><p>Vodafone Limited</p><p>WS Atkins PLC</p>","Aberconwy","Guto Bebb",,"2018-02-20T16:43:06.743Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839167/answer","Biography information for Guto Bebb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839167/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839167/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-02-08","Ministry of Defence: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 25 January 2018 to Question 123536 on Ministry of Defence Procurement, if he will publish the name of each supplier.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","127725"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839168","Scotland Office","false","2018-02-20","<p>The UK Government is committed to working with the Scottish Government, the British Transport Police Authority and the Scottish Police Authority, to ensure that the pensions of officers and staff transferring to Police Scotland are maintained. Scottish Government Ministers have provided assurances to the Scottish Parliament that British Transport Police officers and staff in Scotland will transfer to Police Scotland with their current terms and conditions of service, including pensions.</p><p> </p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2018-02-20T10:08:08.33Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839168/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839168/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839168/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2018-02-08","British Transport Police: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, what assessment he has made of the future viability of the Scottish component of the British Transport Police pension fund when it is transferred to the Scottish Government.","false","Biography information for Ian Murray","Edinburgh South","Ian Murray","127726"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839169","HM Treasury","false","2018-02-20","<p>The Treasury has not issued guidance. The independent financial services regulator - the Financial Conduct Authority (FCA) - requires firms to treat their customers fairly and has broad and robust powers to enforce breaches of its rules.</p><p> </p><p>Confirmed Industry Guidance for the FCA’s Banking Conduct of Business Sourcebook sets out what information firms must provide to customers when they open a joint account, including an explanation of a customer’s rights and duties and the concept of joint and several liability. UK Finance and the Building Societies Association also publish an information leaflet for those considering opening a joint account.</p><p> </p><p>The Government wants to ensure that all victims of domestic abuse are provided with the support they need. The Government will shortly be launching a consultation into tackling domestic abuse, in advance of bringing forward legislation, and I encourage the hon. Member to engage with the consultation when it is published.</p>","Salisbury","John Glen","127729","2018-02-20T12:10:22.86Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839169/answer","Biography information for John Glen","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839169/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839169/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2018-02-08","Domestic Abuse","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether all banks and financial service firms are required to have a written policy on domestic abuse.","false","Biography information for Dr Lisa Cameron","East Kilbride, Strathaven and Lesmahagow","Dr Lisa Cameron","127727"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839170","Department for Transport","false","2018-02-26","<p>At a Westminster Hall Debate last year, the Rt Hon John Hayes MP announced the formation of a Task and Finish group to consider any regulatory issues and remedies. The group’s remit includes considering issues such as those on national standards and whether to provide a statutory definition of plying for hire. The proposal to restrict the locations that taxis and private hire vehicles can carry passenger from or to will also be considered as part of its deliberation.</p><p> </p><p>The group has decided that more time was needed to fully consider the issues but will submit its report shortly.</p>","Wealden","Ms Nusrat Ghani","127730 ; 127732","2018-02-26T14:46:36.803Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839170/answer","Biography information for Ms Nusrat Ghani","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839170/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839170/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-02-08","Taxis","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, if he will make it his policy to take urgent steps in primary legislation to create a statutory definition of cross border hiring whereby a journey must begin or end in the licensing authority area for which the vehicle, driver and operator are licensed; and if he will support this by the introduction of statutory England-wide guidance setting out minimum licensing standards; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","127728"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839171","HM Treasury","false","2018-02-20","<p>The Treasury has not issued guidance. The independent financial services regulator - the Financial Conduct Authority (FCA) - requires firms to treat their customers fairly and has broad and robust powers to enforce breaches of its rules.</p><p> </p><p>Confirmed Industry Guidance for the FCA’s Banking Conduct of Business Sourcebook sets out what information firms must provide to customers when they open a joint account, including an explanation of a customer’s rights and duties and the concept of joint and several liability. UK Finance and the Building Societies Association also publish an information leaflet for those considering opening a joint account.</p><p> </p><p>The Government wants to ensure that all victims of domestic abuse are provided with the support they need. The Government will shortly be launching a consultation into tackling domestic abuse, in advance of bringing forward legislation, and I encourage the hon. Member to engage with the consultation when it is published.</p>","Salisbury","John Glen","127727","2018-02-20T12:10:22.907Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839171/answer","Biography information for John Glen","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839171/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839171/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2018-02-08","Domestic Abuse","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what guidance his Department issued to (a) banks and (b) the financial service sector on responding to cases has of domestic abuse in which the perpetrator and victim have a joint bank accounts.","false","Biography information for Dr Lisa Cameron","East Kilbride, Strathaven and Lesmahagow","Dr Lisa Cameron","127729"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839172","Department for Transport","false","2018-02-26","<p>At a Westminster Hall Debate last year, the Rt Hon John Hayes MP announced the formation of a Task and Finish group to consider any regulatory issues and remedies. The group’s remit includes considering issues such as those on national standards and whether to provide a statutory definition of plying for hire. The proposal to restrict the locations that taxis and private hire vehicles can carry passenger from or to will also be considered as part of its deliberation.</p><p> </p><p>The group has decided that more time was needed to fully consider the issues but will submit its report shortly.</p>","Wealden","Ms Nusrat Ghani","127728 ; 127732","2018-02-26T14:46:36.867Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839172/answer","Biography information for Ms Nusrat Ghani","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839172/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839172/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-02-08","Taxis","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, if he will bring forward legislative proposals for a definition of plying for hire.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","127730"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839173","Scotland Office","false","2018-02-20","<p>The UK Government is working closely with the Scottish Government as well as the two police forces and police authorities through a Joint Programme Board, to ensure that effective arrangements are in place for cross-border railway policing once responsibilities have been transferred, so that we continue to have a railway policing service which protects the safety of passengers.</p><p> </p><p>The direct costs of the transfer are being borne by the British Transport Police Authority which is wholly funded by the railway operators. The current estimated cost of the transfer to the Authority, which includes the costs of the British Transport Police, is £1.17m. Post-merger it is expected that the aggregate costs for railway operators of charges for policing from the British Transport Police and Police Scotland will be similar to current costs. Future policing charges in Scotland will be a matter for the Scottish Police Authority.</p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2018-02-20T10:11:34.76Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839173/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839173/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839173/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2018-02-08","British Transport Police: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, what assessment he has made of the effect of the merger of the Scottish component of the British Transport Police into Police Scotland on cross border policing; and what estimate he has made of the cost of cross border activities as a result of that merger.","false","Biography information for Ian Murray","Edinburgh South","Ian Murray","127731"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839174","Department for Transport","false","2018-02-26","<p>At a Westminster Hall Debate last year, the Rt Hon John Hayes MP announced the formation of a Task and Finish group to consider any regulatory issues and remedies. The group’s remit includes considering issues such as those on national standards and whether to provide a statutory definition of plying for hire. The proposal to restrict the locations that taxis and private hire vehicles can carry passenger from or to will also be considered as part of its deliberation.</p><p> </p><p>The group has decided that more time was needed to fully consider the issues but will submit its report shortly.</p>","Wealden","Ms Nusrat Ghani","127728 ; 127730","2018-02-26T14:46:36.913Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839174/answer","Biography information for Ms Nusrat Ghani","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839174/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839174/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-02-08","Taxis","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, pursuant to the Answer of 24 October 2018 to Question 108783 on Taxis, on what date in the New Year the working group plans to report.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","127732"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839175","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-02-20","<p>During the Child Maintenance application process, clients can identify to us that they were subject to domestic violence. Whilst we do not specifically advise clients on domestic violence, caseworkers across both Child Maintenance Service and Child Support Agency are trained to signpost clients to relevant organisations where appropriate. In addition, more detailed training will be rolled out beginning 5<sup>th</sup> March to over 4000 CMS caseworkers, which has been designed, working with partner organisations, to help caseworkers handle calls sensitively, understand and recognise domestic abuse, and respond appropriately to clients who are victims of domestic abuse.</p>","North West Hampshire","Kit Malthouse",,"2018-02-20T10:59:20.027Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839175/answer","Biography information for Kit Malthouse","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839175/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839175/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-02-08","Child Maintenance Service: Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, with reference to his Department's Response to the Work and Pension Committee’s Fourteenth Report of Session 2016–17, Child Maintenance: Government Response to the House of Commons, HC 354, how many employees within the Child Maintenance Service have received specialist domestic abuse training.","false","Biography information for Dr Lisa Cameron","East Kilbride, Strathaven and Lesmahagow","Dr Lisa Cameron","127733"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839176","HM Treasury","false","2018-02-26","<p>In 2011, the approximate aggregate value at the time the funds were frozen in the UK was £7.5 billion.</p><p> </p><p>The current value of frozen assets held are in the process of being finalised as part of the “2017 Annual Frozen Fund Review”. However, at the close of business on 30 September 2016 they were approximately £11.7 billion. The figure is provided on an aggregate basis so as not to indirectly disclose the value of funds held by particular individuals or entities.</p><p> </p><p>The frozen funds continue to belong to the individuals and entities listed under the Regulation and are not seized or otherwise held by HM Government.</p>","Salisbury","John Glen",,"2018-02-26T13:53:13.547Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839176/answer","Biography information for John Glen","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839176/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839176/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2018-02-08","Freezing of Assets: Libya","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, with reference to decision of the UN to freeze Libyan Assets, agreed by EU Directive and adopted by the UK, whether he has made an estimate of the value of assets frozen (a) at the time the assets were frozen and (b) the current value of those assets.","false","Biography information for Jim Fitzpatrick","Poplar and Limehouse","Jim Fitzpatrick","127734"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839177","Scotland Office","false","2018-02-20","<p>The UK Government is working closely with the Scottish Government as well as the two police forces and police authorities through a Joint Programme Board. A central, ongoing focus of that Board is to deliver a seamless and orderly transfer of responsibilities and to ensure that the overall level of policing, including policing across the border, remains fully effective so that we continue to have a railway policing service which protects the safety of passengers.</p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2018-02-20T10:12:52.81Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839177/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839177/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839177/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2018-02-08","British Transport Police: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, what assessment he has made of the effect on cross border policing of the proposed merger of British Transport Police (Scotland) with Police Scotland.","false","Biography information for Ian Murray","Edinburgh South","Ian Murray","127735"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839178","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-02-20","<p>Training for DWP staff in front line roles provides face to face and e-learning modules on how we can best serve our vulnerable customers, including victims of domestic abuse. Frontline staff are also trained to refer customers to appropriate specialist support.</p><p> </p>","North West Hampshire","Kit Malthouse",,"2018-02-20T12:08:59.913Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839178/answer","Biography information for Kit Malthouse","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839178/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839178/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-02-08","Department for Work and Pensions: Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, whether (a) specialist, (b) face to face and (c) ongoing training on domestic abuse is provided to employees working in its frontline services.","false","Biography information for Dr Lisa Cameron","East Kilbride, Strathaven and Lesmahagow","Dr Lisa Cameron","127736"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839179","Home Office","false","2018-02-20","<p>We do not routinely comment on whether an organisation is or is not under consideration for proscription.</p>","Wyre and Preston North","Mr Ben Wallace",,"2018-02-20T11:16:23.247Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839179/answer","Biography information for Mr Ben Wallace","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839179/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839179/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-02-08","Antifa","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, if she will proscribe Antifa; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Desmond Swayne","New Forest West","Sir Desmond Swayne","127737"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839180","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-02-20","<p>As a member of the United Nations Security Council Committee established pursuant to resolution 1970 (2011) concerning Libya, we regularly discuss the implementation of the UN Libya sanctions regime, including with EU members of the Committee. We have regular discussions on the EU autonomous regime with EU member states in the relevant working groups and the listings are reviewed on a regular basis. We have also done so in routine working group meetings with EU partners concerning the implementation of the EU Regulations and restrictive measures on Libya. By its Resolution 2362 of 29 June 2017, the UN Security Council reaffirmed its intention to ensure that assets frozen by the UN in 2011 shall at a later stage be made available to and for the benefit of the Libyan people.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-02-20T17:34:09.847Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839180/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839180/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839180/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-02-08","Libya: Freezing of Assets","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what discussions he has held with his counterparts in the EU on tensuring the security and retention of frozen Libyan assets.","false","Biography information for Jim Fitzpatrick","Poplar and Limehouse","Jim Fitzpatrick","127738"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839181","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-02-20","<p>​The Foreign and Commonwealth Office does not hold information on the numbers of Ambassadors and High Commissioners that have left posts and subsequently been re-appointed as an official or consultant. This information cannot be provided without exceeding the disproportionate cost threshold.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2018-02-20T17:01:06.553Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839181/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839181/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839181/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-02-08","Diplomatic Service: Labour Turnover","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, how many Ambassadors and High Commissioners have left posts with his Department and subsequently been re-appointed as an official or consultant since 2010.","false","Biography information for Ian Murray","Edinburgh South","Ian Murray","127739"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839182","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-02-20","<p>Since the Dartford Crossing was reclassified as an urban road by the Department for Transport, this section of road has been included in Defra’s air quality modelling.</p><p> </p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2018-02-20T18:47:52.347Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839182/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839182/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839182/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-02-08","Dartford-Thurrock Crossing: Air Pollution","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what progress he has made on including the Dartford Crossing in his Department’s Air Quality Plan as a result of the reclassification of that crossing as an urban road in 2017.","false","Biography information for Sue Hayman","Workington","Sue Hayman","127740"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839183","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-02-20","<p>Our UK plan for tackling roadside nitrogen dioxide (NO<sub>2</sub>) concentrations was informed by modelling which uses the latest available evidence, which indicates that all modelled roads in Dartford are expected to be compliant with the NO<sub>2</sub> limit value by 2018.</p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2018-02-20T17:54:18.953Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839183/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839183/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839183/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-02-08","Air Pollution: Dartford","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, for what reasons his Department's Air Quality Action Plan concluded that no road in Dartford would be over the limit value for air pollution this year.","false","Biography information for Sue Hayman","Workington","Sue Hayman","127741"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839184","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-02-20","<p>The A206.</p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2018-02-20T17:57:24.33Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839184/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839184/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839184/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-02-08","Air Pollution: Dartford","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, which road in Dartford was identified in his Department’s Air Quality Action Plan to be over the limit value for air pollution in 2017.","false","Biography information for Sue Hayman","Workington","Sue Hayman","127742"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839185","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-02-20","<p>The local government finance settlement for 2018-19, approved by the House on 7 February, allocated additional resources to local authorities to eliminate so-called ‘negative Revenue Support Grant’ (RSG) in that year. I acknowledge concerns around negative RSG in 2019 to 2020 and we will be looking at fair and affordable options that will address the problem. I plan to formally consult on proposals in the Spring, ahead of next year’s settlement</p>","Richmond (Yorks)","Rishi Sunak",,"2018-02-20T12:36:18.96Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839185/answer","Biography information for Rishi Sunak","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839185/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839185/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-02-08","Local Government Finance: Dorset","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, pursuant to his oral contribution of 7 February 2018, Official Report, column 1566, on Local Government Finance, if he will encourage local authorities in Dorset to budget for 2018-19 on the basis that they will not be subject to negative revenue support grant in 2019-20; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Christopher Chope","Christchurch","Sir Christopher Chope","127743"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839186","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-02-20","<p>We are aware of reports that Israel has resumed supplying additional electricity to Gaza following an official request by the Palestinian Authority. This has increased supply from an average of four hours a day to six hours per day. We remain concerned about the humanitarian situation in Gaza and continue to monitor it closely. The UK will continue to urge all the parties to take the necessary practical steps to improve conditions in Gaza, including restoring the availability of electricity as a matter of urgency.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-02-20T16:24:31.893Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839186/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839186/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839186/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-02-08","Gaza: Fuels","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what information his Department holds on fuel supplies for back-up generators in Gaza; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","127744"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839187","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-02-23","<p>In 2017 Public Health England and Sport England established a co-funded, multi-component partnership called the Moving Healthcare Professional Programme (MHPP) which increases awareness and skills of health professionals to embed activity within routine care.</p><p> </p><p>A component of MHPP includes the peer-to-peer Clinical Champions work-stream which is focused on developing the skills of health professionals to deliver brief advice on physical activity as part of routine care. This programme has trained over 5,000 healthcare professionals across the whole programme, the majority of whom are general practitioners in training.</p><p> </p><p>In 2013, the National Institute for Health and Care Excellence published guidance recommending that healthcare professionals integrate brief advice on physical activity into routine clinical practice.</p><p> </p><p>The United Kingdom Chief Medical Officers’ guidelines for physical activity include daily or weekly quantities of physical activity of at least moderate intensity, for example 150 minutes per week for adults.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2018-02-23T12:50:13.66Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839187/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839187/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839187/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-02-08","General Practitioners","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what guidance his Department has issued to GPs to promote participation in sport to their patients.","false","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Tom Watson","127745"
