"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839190","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-02-21","<p>The Ministry of Justice records defects of the contract where there have been deficiencies in the service delivered by contractors. These are flagged to the contractor so that they can correct them in a timely manner. We keep all our contracts under a robust monitoring system. Defects have been reported to Carillion 578 and Amey 299 times since the start of the contract in June 2015.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2018-02-21T18:11:38.647Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839190/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839190/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839190/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-02-08","Amey and Carillion","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many recorded breaches of contracts by (a) Carillion and (b) Amey there were in financial year 2016-17.","false","Biography information for David Hanson","Delyn","David Hanson","127748"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839191","Department for International Development","false","2018-02-20","<p>UK financial assistance to the Palestinian Authority helps to pay the salaries of vetted health public servants in the West Bank, providing up to 3,700 immunisations for children and around 185,000 medical consultations annually. The UK is a long-term supporter of the United Nations Relief and Works Agency (UNRWA), which provides basic services, including basic healthcare, to over 800,000 Palestinian refugees in the West Bank and 1.3 million Palestinian refugees in Gaza. In addition, the UK is supporting approximately 1 million Gazans by providing clean water, rehabilitating sanitation facilities and promoting hygiene standards to stop the spread of disease through the United Nations Children’s Fund (UNICEF).</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-02-20T14:25:51.123Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839191/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839191/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839191/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2018-02-08","Gaza and West Bank: Health Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what steps her Department is taking improve health provision for communities in (a) the West Bank and (b) Gaza.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","127749"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839192","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-02-20","<p>As of 1 December 2017, the total recorded built assets held by the Ministry of Defence (MOD) was 29,098,652 square metres in the UK and 3,384,571 square metres overseas. The net internal useable area (floor space) of built assets is not held.</p><p>The Department is currently reviewing the data it holds regarding the Defence estate to assure the information reflects the current position.</p><p>The MOD's Information Management System (IMS) does not hold information on built assets held by the MOD for each of the last five years.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2018-02-20T17:04:51.457Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839192/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839192/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839192/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-02-08","Ministry of Defence: Buildings","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the size of his Department's estate was in square metres of floor space for each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","127750"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839193","Cabinet Office","false","2018-02-26","<p>The State of the Estate report, published annually, provides information on the efficiency and sustainability of the central civil estate, including the size and cost of the Estate.</p><p>The State of the Estate report 2015 -2016 is available online at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/state-of-the-estate-report-2015-to-2016" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/state-of-the-estate-report-2015-to-2016</a></p><p>A breakdown by Department, in square metres of floor space at March 2016 is available at Annex B.</p><p>The State of the Estate report 2016 - 2017, due to be published shortly, will provide details of further progress made in reducing the size and cost of the estate, including a departmental breakdown of floor space at 31 March 2017.</p>","Hertsmere","Oliver Dowden",,"2018-02-26T17:04:01.34Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839193/answer","Biography information for Oliver Dowden","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839193/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839193/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-02-08","Government Departments: Buildings","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what the current size of the Government estate is, by Department, in square metres of floor space.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","127751"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839194","Cabinet Office","false","2018-03-20","<p>The State of the Estate report, published annually, provides information on the efficiency and sustainability of the central civil estate, including the size and cost of the Estate.</p><p> </p><p>The State of Estate reports from 2010 - 2014 are available online at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/state-of-the-estate" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/state-of-the-estate</a></p><p>The State of the Estate report 2015 -2016 is available online at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/state-of-the-estate-report-2015-to-2016" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/state-of-the-estate-report-2015-to-2016</a></p><p> </p><p>A departmental breakdown is available at Annex B for each corresponding year.</p><p> </p><p>The State of the Estate report 2016 - 2017 is due to be published shortly.</p>","Hertsmere","Oliver Dowden",,"2018-03-20T11:18:34.73Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839194/answer","Biography information for Oliver Dowden","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839194/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839194/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-02-08","Government Departments: Buildings","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what the size of the Government estate was, by Department, in square metres of floor space in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","127752"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839195","Department for Transport","false","2018-02-20","<p>The decision to provide Network Rail Infrastructure Limited with the legal powers to construct, operate and maintain new passing facilities and associated railway infrastructure on the Hope Valley route between Bamford and Hathersage and at Dore was issued on 13 February 2018. A copy of the decision letter and the Inspector’s report, following the public Inquiry, can be found at the following link: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/twa-inspector-reports-and-decision-letters" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/twa-inspector-reports-and-decision-letters</a>.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2018-02-20T10:48:04.507Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839195/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839195/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839195/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-02-08","Railways: North West","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what the timetable is for the publication of the results of the 2016 public enquiry into the Hope Valley line improvements.","false","Biography information for Mr Clive Betts","Sheffield South East","Mr Clive Betts","127753"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839196","Department for Transport","false","2018-02-20","<p>On 13 February 2018, the Secretary of State announced his decision to provide Network Rail Infrastructure Limited with the legal powers to construct, operate and maintain new passing facilities and associated railway infrastructure on the Hope Valley route between Bamford and Hathersage and at Dore. Network Rail have completed the single option design for the railway infrastructure scheme proposed in the Hope Valley and, following last week’s decision, the timetable for further work on this scheme will be announced in due course.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2018-02-20T15:53:45.06Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839196/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839196/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839196/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-02-08","Railways: North West","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what the timetable is for Network Rail's design work on the improvements to the Hope Valley line be concluded.","false","Biography information for Mr Clive Betts","Sheffield South East","Mr Clive Betts","127754"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839198","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-02-20","<p>The information on non-payroll staff is published and can be found on the gov.uk website at the link below:</p><p>https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/workforce-management-information-mod</p><p>Information for May to December 2017 will be published by the Cabinet Office.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2018-02-20T17:06:44.087Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839198/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839198/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839198/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-02-08","Ministry of Defence: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the monthly civilian staff cost to his Department was for (a) payroll and (b) non-payroll staff, including (i) contingency and (ii) consultancy staff in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","127755"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839199","Department for Education","false","2018-02-21","<p>The Department has not made a specific assessment of the efficacy and effectiveness of Designated Safeguarding Leads (DSLs). Guidance for inspectors reflects the requirements for DSLs and inspectors report on whether arrangements in schools for safeguarding children are effective.</p><p> </p><p>The green paper ‘Transforming Children and Young People’s Mental Health provision’ proposes to incentivise schools and colleges to put in place a Designated Senior Lead for mental health. Around half of schools already have a dedicated lead for mental health. The green paper proposal leaves flexibility for schools to decide on the role that the mental health lead should play and how it fits with the safeguarding lead and commits to review how schools’ approaches to mental health and wellbeing is reflected in existing statutory policies, including safeguarding. The paper is available to view here: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/consultations/transforming-children-and-young-peoples-mental-health-provision-a-green-paper" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/consultations/transforming-children-and-young-peoples-mental-health-provision-a-green-paper</a>.</p><p> </p><p>An independent evaluation of the Government’s mental health services and schools link programme showed that school leads working with counterparts in the NHS have had considerable success in strengthening joint working and improving referrals between schools and health services. The independent evaluation is available to view here: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/590242/Evaluation_of_the_MH_services_and_schools_link_pilots-RR.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/590242/Evaluation_of_the_MH_services_and_schools_link_pilots-RR.pdf</a>.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2018-02-21T12:52:57.29Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839199/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839199/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839199/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-02-08","Schools: Mental Health Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, whether the Government has made an assessment of the (a) efficacy and (b) experiences of Designated Safeguarding Leads in schools in advance of the introduction of Designated Mental Health Leads in schools.","false","Biography information for Mr Barry Sheerman","Huddersfield","Mr Barry Sheerman","127756"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839200","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-02-20","<p>The information on non-payroll staff is published and can be found on the gov.uk website at the link below:</p><p>https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/workforce-management-information-mod</p><p>Information for May to December 2017 will be published by the Cabinet Office.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2018-02-20T17:05:25.483Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839200/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839200/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839200/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-02-08","Ministry of Defence: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many non-payroll staff were employed by his Department in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","127757"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839201","Department for Transport","false","2018-02-21","<p>The Department’s value for money assessment includes assumptions about the financial merits of increasing the number of fast trains on this route. This assessment will need to be refreshed as part of taking forward further work on this scheme. Decisions about future franchise changes will be assessed on their merits as part of this further work.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2018-02-21T17:12:42.337Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839201/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839201/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839201/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-02-08","Railways: North West","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether he has made an assessment of the potential financial merits of including in the Hope Valley improvement scheme an increase in express trains from Sheffield to Manchester from 2 to 4 trains an hour.","false","Biography information for Mr Clive Betts","Sheffield South East","Mr Clive Betts","127758"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839202","Department for Transport","false","2018-02-21","<p>On 13 February 2018, the Secretary of State announced his decision to provide Network Rail Infrastructure Limited with the legal powers to construct, operate and maintain new passing facilities and associated railway infrastructure on the Hope Valley route between Bamford and Hathersage and at Dore. The Department’s value for money assessment guidance includes guidance for the assessment of benefits to the economy.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2018-02-21T17:09:09.537Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839202/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839202/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839202/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-02-08","Railways: North West","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether he has made an assessment of the effect of the Hope Valley line improvement scheme on economic growth in the area.","false","Biography information for Mr Clive Betts","Sheffield South East","Mr Clive Betts","127759"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839204","Department for Transport","false","2018-02-22","<p>On 13 February 2018, the Secretary of State announced his decision to provide Network Rail Infrastructure Limited with the legal powers to construct, operate and maintain new passing facilities and associated railway infrastructure on the Hope Valley route between Bamford and Hathersage and at Dore. Network Rail have completed the single option design for the railway infrastructure scheme proposed in the Hope Valley and, following last week’s decision, the timetable for further work on this scheme including a final investment decision will be announced in due course.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2018-02-22T16:05:45.037Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839204/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839204/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839204/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-02-08","Railways: North West","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what the timetable is for a decision to be made on the funding for the Hope Valley Line improvement scheme.","false","Biography information for Mr Clive Betts","Sheffield South East","Mr Clive Betts","127760"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839205","Department for Transport","false","2018-02-20","<p>It will be for the bidders to determine their fleet strategy to meet the requirements of the Invitation to Tender when it is issued.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2018-02-20T14:21:43.643Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839205/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839205/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839205/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-02-08","Midland Main Railway Line: Rolling Stock","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what the timetable is for new rolling stock to be introduced on the Midland Mainline.","false","Biography information for Mr Clive Betts","Sheffield South East","Mr Clive Betts","127761"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839206","Home Office","false","2018-02-20","<p>The Home Office collects and publishes information on the number of persons detained under section 136 of the Mental Health Act 1983, including information on where the person is detained, and whether they are under 18 or aged 18 years and over.</p><p> </p><p>These data were first collected in 2016/17 and published as part of the ‘Police powers and procedures, England and Wales’ statistical bulletin, which can be accessed here: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/police-powers-and-procedures-england-and-wales-year-ending-31-march-2017" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/police-powers-and-procedures-england-and-wales-year-ending-31-march-2017</a></p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2018-02-20T16:58:32.043Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839206/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839206/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839206/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-02-08","Police Custody: Mental Illness","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many (a) children and (b) adults spent time in a police station as a place of safety due to a mental health condition in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","127762"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839207","Department for Transport","false","2018-02-20","<p>It will be for the bidders to determine their fleet strategy to meet the requirements of the Invitation to Tender when it is issued. However, these bi-mode trains will improve journeys sooner, without the need for wires and masts on the whole route, and with less disruptive engineering works for passengers. Customers will also benefit from the wider upgrade to the Midland Mainline, which includes line speed improvements to reduce journey times.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2018-02-20T15:57:53.07Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839207/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839207/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839207/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-02-08","Midland Main Railway Line: Rolling Stock","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what the timetable is for hybrid trains to begin running on the Midland Mainline.","false","Biography information for Mr Clive Betts","Sheffield South East","Mr Clive Betts","127763"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839208","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-02-20","<p>The table below shows the number of accident and emergency (A&amp;E) attendances in 2016-17 where patients presented after deliberate self-harm for all diagnoses and the attendance rate per 100,000 population.</p><p>Activity in English National Health Service hospitals and English NHS commissioned activity in the independent sector.</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p>A&amp;E Attendances</p></td><td><p>Rate per 100,000 population</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Self-harm (all diagnoses)</p></td><td><p>111,406</p></td><td><p>201.6</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>Source: Hospital Episode Statistics (HES), NHS Digital <a href="http://content.digital.nhs.uk/hes" target="_blank">http://content.digital.nhs.uk/hes</a></p><p>Data regarding the number of A&amp;E patients that undergo a psychological assessment is not collected centrally.</p><p> </p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price",,"2018-02-20T17:25:06.74Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839208/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839208/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839208/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-02-08","Accident and Emergency Departments: Self-harm","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, how many attendances at emergency departments for self-harm per 100,000 people there were in 2016-17; and how many of those attendancies received a psychological assessment.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","127764"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839209","Cabinet Office","false","2018-04-16","<p>This information is already in the public domain. Please refer to published accounts with links as per below.</p><p> </p><p>2016-17 - page 47</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/646841/CO_Annual_Report_2016-17.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/646841/CO_Annual_Report_2016-17.pdf</a></p><p> </p><p>2015-16 - page 54</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/536577/Cabinet-Office-annual-report-2015-2016.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/536577/Cabinet-Office-annual-report-2015-2016.pdf</a></p><p> </p><p>2014-15 – page 111</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/465137/Cabinet_Office_Annual_Report_and_Accounts_2014-15_-_Web_Accessible_Version.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/465137/Cabinet_Office_Annual_Report_and_Accounts_2014-15_-_Web_Accessible_Version.pdf</a></p><p> </p><p>2013-14 – page 112</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/325328/41432_HC_Cabinet_Office_annual_report_2013-14_accessible.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/325328/41432_HC_Cabinet_Office_annual_report_2013-14_accessible.pdf</a></p><p> </p><p>2012-13 - page 143</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/225980/HC_15.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/225980/HC_15.pdf</a></p>","Hertsmere","Oliver Dowden",,"2018-04-16T14:16:06.883Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839209/answer","Biography information for Oliver Dowden","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839209/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839209/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-02-08","Government Departments: Operating Costs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what the (a) planned and (b) actual administration budget spending for each Department has been in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","127765"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839210","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-02-20","<p>Data regarding the number of in-patient eating disorder beds is not available for each year since 2010.</p><p> </p><p>The latest management data available shows that the number of specialist eating disorder beds for adults is 415 (as at January 2017) and the number for children and young people is 220 (as at April 2017).</p><p> </p><p>Children and young people with eating disorders are routinely and appropriately admitted to other types of Child and Adolescent Mental Health Services (CAMHS) in-patient services. NHS England is currently undertaking a programme of work to redistribute CAMHS beds across the country to open beds in underserved areas of the country and strengthen integration with local pathways.</p><p> </p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price",,"2018-02-20T17:15:10.22Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839210/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839210/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839210/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-02-08","Eating Disorders","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, how many in-patient eating disorder beds there have been for (a) adults and (b) children in each year since 2010 in England.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","127766"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839211","Department of Health and Social Care","true","2018-02-20","<p>NHS Digital is the organisation responsible for collecting and publishing National Health Service complaints data. These data were collected annually until 1 April 2015. NHS Digital now collects these data quarterly and monthly data are not available. The attached tables show quarterly data received in respect of NHS mental health services for the periods requested.</p><p> </p><p>Because of changes to the method and frequency of the data collection NHS Digital currently classify data from April 2015 as ‘experimental’ so they cannot be compared with previous years.</p><p> </p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price",,"2018-02-20T17:13:41.133Z","2018-02-26T12:38:13.31Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839211/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839211/answer","PQ127767 NHS Complaints Data.xlsx","NHS Complaints Data","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839211/answer","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839211/answer/previousversion/42074","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-02-08","Health Services: Complaints","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, how many formal complaints (a) mental health services and (b) the NHS received in each region in each month of each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","127767"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839212","Prime Minister","false","2018-02-26","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the press release issued on 1 February following my meeting with President Xi and which is available on the <a href="http://gov.uk" target="_blank">gov.uk</a> website: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/news/pm-meeting-with-president-xi-1-february-2018" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/news/pm-meeting-with-president-xi-1-february-2018</a>.</p>","Maidenhead","Mrs Theresa May",,"2018-02-26T16:45:55.893Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839212/answer","Biography information for Mrs Theresa May","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839212/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/839212/answer",,,,,"23","Prime Minister","Prime Minister","2018-02-08","Hong Kong: Elections","1","House of Commons","To ask the Prime Minister, whether she discussed the disqualification of candidates from Hong Kong elections with the Government of China during her recent visit to that country.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","127768"
